    exact ⟨0, by simp_all [completes_aux, iat, HistoryEquality]⟩
  -- Since the function output is 0, we can directly use this result to show the completeness.
  simpa [completes_aux, iat, HistoryEquality] using h₁
``` 

This proof correctly uses the completeness of the function output (which is always 0) to satisfy the given conditions by choosing the index 0. The simplifications and the choice of index are straightforward based on the constant nature of the output. The proof is thus complete.
